# shadcn/ui Components

This project uses **shadcn/ui** for all UI elements. Never use raw HTML elements or other UI libraries when a shadcn/ui component is available.

## Initialization

If shadcn/ui is not yet initialized in the project, run:

```bash
npx shadcn@latest init
```

## Adding Components

If a component is not installed, add it before using it:

```bash
npx shadcn@latest add <component-name>
```

Examples:
```bash
npx shadcn@latest add button
npx shadcn@latest add input
npx shadcn@latest add card
```

## Usage

Import components from `@/components/ui/`:

```tsx
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button"
import { Input } from "@/components/ui/input"
```

- Always check if a shadcn/ui component exists before building a custom one
- Do not install or use other UI libraries (e.g. MUI, Chakra, Ant Design) for components shadcn/ui covers
